snippet.textDisplay:
This nav screen was definitely not the pinnacle of tech back in 2012
I drove a 2012 VW Tiguan back in the day and we still have it now as a second car. But the screen of it is absolutely useable and not too far behind something that comes out today. I can compare it to a 2019 cayenne and the cayennes is better with better resolution and overall quality but its not like the 2012 screen is unuseable. You can do zooming, typing and all that just fine and respond time is really quick.
VW had one of the best infotainment systems back in the day

snippet.textDisplay: The US Department Of Energy approved up to $529 Million loan to Henrick Fisker  to start an environmentally sustainable car  company .  He took $192 Million  and started a company which had few patents and used off the shelf parts from GM ,  Unused electric car tech .  After creating a car that resembled a dead catfish, sales were lack luster .  Upon failure of the company,  the US Congress wanted to know what happened .  Congress was not in the Venture Capital business, so they were not familiar with the corrupt nature of the  “ Start - Up” culture , if that is the case , they might as well have funded Uber !    All of the $$$ went to Executive salary , a few bucks built a car  , then they laughed all the way to the bank !
